cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.RO 

The paper deals with generating 3D shapes from limited sensor data, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed solution involves a generative recurrent neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of primitives to represent shapes is also relevant to computer graphics (cs.GR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the application of the proposed method to robotics (cs.RO) is mentioned in the abstract.
